General purpose support Support for cluster resource managers (RM).
Currently TORQUE and SLURM RMs are supported. SGE and LSF support is planned for near future.

This module is tested against Open MPI MPI2 implementation.

EXAMPLES: 
To enable DMTCP RM module you need to put --rm option in dmtcp_launch. Sample scripts for 
SLURM can be found below. TORQUE scripts can be constructed in similar fashion.
During debug it is better to start dmtcp_coordinator on interactive terminal on frontend. In
batch script you should remove coordinator startup line and put appropriate hostname in dmtcp_launch 
'-h' option.

* Sample SLURM batch script for initial program run:

--------------------------------- SNIP -------------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/sh
#SBATCH --ntasks=XXXX
#SBATCH ...
  
hostname

# If you install DMTCP in your user directory (not cluster-wide) you need to extend PATH variable:
export PATH="<path-to-dmtcp-installation>:$PATH

# Start dmtcp_coordinator (Fix if debugging or using coordinator on frontend)
dmtcp_coordinator &

# DMTCP coordinator needs to be started on localhost. Or put other host in -h option
dmtcp_launch --rm -h `hostname` <other-dmtcp-options> mpirun <mpi-options> ./mpi

--------------------------------- SNIP -------------------------------------------------------------

* Sample SLURM batch script for program restart:

--------------------------------- SNIP -------------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/sh
#SBATCH --ntasks=XXXX
#SBATCH ...
  
hostname

# If you install DMTCP in your user directory (not cluster-wide) you need to extend PATH variable:
export PATH="<path-to-dmtcp-installation>:$PATH

# Start dmtcp_coordinator (Fix if debugging or using coordinator on frontend)
dmtcp_coordinator &
export DMTCP_HOST=`hostname`

./dmtcp_restart_script.sh

--------------------------------- SNIP -------------------------------------------------------------

